      • openWorkbook

        public static Workbook openWorkbook(java.io.File file)
                             throws java.io.IOException
        Open workbook file.

        This method inspects the file name extension to determine which factory should be used for loading. If there are multiple factories registered for the extension, the matching factories are tried in sequential order. If loading succeeds, the workbook is returned.

        Parameters:
        file - the workbook file
        Returns:
        the workbook loaded from file
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if workbook could not be loaded

      • showDialogAndSaveWorkbook

        public static java.net.URI showDialogAndSaveWorkbook(java.awt.Component parent,
                                                     Workbook workbook,
                                                     java.io.File file)
                                              throws java.io.IOException
        Show file selection dialog and save workbook.

        A file selection dialog is shown and the workbook is saved to the selected file. If the file already exists, a confirmation dialog is shown, asking the user whether to overwrite the file.

        Parameters:
        parent - the parent component for the dialog
        workbook - the workbook to save
        file - the file to set the default path in the dialog
        Returns:
        the URI the file was saved to or null if the user canceled the dialog
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if an exception occurs while saving

      • getFileExtension

        public static java.lang.String getFileExtension(java.io.File file)
        Extract file extension.

        The file extension is the part of the filename from the last dot to the end (including the dot). The extension of the file /foo/bar/file.txt is ".txt".

        If the filename doesn't contain a dot, the extension is the empty string ("").

        Parameters:
        file - the file
        Returns:
        the file extension including the dot.
